2001-11-26 Monday 10:02  tobi

	* config.c (1.47), init.c (1.29), msged.h (1.33), readmail.c
	(1.41), template.c (1.6), template.h (1.2), doc/whatsnew.txt
	(1.69), doc/manual/msged.texi (1.57): "Switch XXLTearline on" by A.
	Ilchenko. If you set this, you can have a tearline of up to 79
	characters (instead of 35), and the Unix version will print system
	information in the tearline.  But be aware that this violates FTSC
	rules, so using this is discouraged.

